Rules for Inclusion:
Original Peer-Reviewed Research Study: The abstract must outline an original peer-reviewed research study. Abstracts summarizing past studies or publications are excluded.
Participant Criteria: The abstract must include participants with:
Dementia with Lewy bodies (DLB)
Parkinson’s disease dementia (PDD)
Lewy body dementia (LBD)
Prodromal dementia with Lewy bodies
Parkinson’s disease with mild cognitive impairment
Lewy body mild cognitive impairment
Parkinsonism-dementia (PDD)
Risk Factor or Predictor Reported: The abstract must report at least one risk factor or predictor correlated with the mentioned disease.
Publication in English: The abstract must be written in English.
Human Participants: The study must include human participants, often referred to as "patients" or "participants". Studies involving animals other than humans are excluded.
Exclude Studies Without Cognitive Impairment: Exclude studies that only involve people with a Lewy body disease without cognitive impairment (Parkinson’s disease without dementia or mild cognitive impairment, prodromal Parkinson’s disease without cognitive impairment).
Exclude Past Experiment Results Only: If the abstract mentions research results only from past experiments and does not indicate that new experiments were executed, it should be excluded.
Parkinsonism with Dementia: If "parkinsonism" as a word appears and "dementia" as a word is mentioned a couple of words later, it should be included as the abstract refers to Parkinson’s disease dementia (PDD).